article.headline: CS Northridge 91, UC Davis 74
article.story: LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Thomas Shewmake scored a career-high 25 points and pulled down 10 rebounds as Cal State Northridge beat UC Davis 91-74 Wednesday night. The senior Shewmake had a career high in points and a double-double for the second straight game. He had 24 points and 15 rebounds Saturday against Cal State Fullerton. Jonathan Heard came off the bench to score 21 points and shot 9-for-11 from the free-throw line. Shewmake and Heard combined for more than half of the Matadors' points. Rob Haynes added 11 points and Jayme Miller scored 10 points for Northridge (12-13). UC Davis (4-19) has lost seven straight since beating Northridge in double overtime on Jan. 18. Vince Oliver scored a game-high 28 points for the Aggies. He scored a career-high 30 in the January win over the Matadors. C.J. Portz scored 14 points for UC Davis and Dominic Calegari added 10.
